The paper deals with efficient implementation of a massive MIMO system with FDD operation, which involves channel state information (CSI) estimation and feedback. This falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The proposed method also involves sparsity-based techniques, which are commonly used in compressed sensing (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.MM). Finally, the paper deals with system optimization and design, which falls under the category of control and optimization (cs.SY).
